                            <comment id="491733" author="bzzz" created="Mon, 23 Mar 2026 19:03:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;unfortunately, none of the backtraces above actually was running a transaction - they were at declaration or waiting for new txg to start. there was another thread actually running transaction and holding current txg open (but not allowing new threads to join due to size/time limit).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="491727" author="defazio" created="Mon, 23 Mar 2026 18:47:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;We didn&apos;t capture the stacks while this issue was present. The admins were rebooting the nodes that were stuck. The only stacks we have are the ones that made it into the console logs due to timeouts.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="491642" author="bzzz" created="Sat, 21 Mar 2026 18:37:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&amp;gt; zfs txgs not advancing&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;this means there was a thread holding txg open (i.e. running a transaction).&lt;br/&gt;
this is why I asked for all backtraces - to find that one.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="491626" author="defazio" created="Fri, 20 Mar 2026 18:19:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve added some debug logs some of the MDT nodes&lt;br/&gt;
our normal debug mask is &quot;debug=ioctl neterror warning error emerg config console snapshot&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
The files called  *debug-all had &quot;debug=-1&quot;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="491620" author="defazio" created="Fri, 20 Mar 2026 17:14:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This issue is not currently happening. It was only on 2026-03-18 that it was observed to cause major problems.&lt;br/&gt;
We suspected that quota enforcement may have been an issue due to the stack traces. We turned on quota enforcement for user quotas for both block and inodes somewhat recently on 2026-02-02.&lt;br/&gt;
We turned all quota enforcement off for the affected file system at about 2026-03-18 14:50 local time. unix timestamp ~1773870600&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;After turning off quota enforcement, we still had to reboot yuba4 which was stuck (zfs txgs not advancing). The admins dealt with connection issues from the client side after that, and the file system has been functioning normally since then.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="491594" author="bzzz" created="Fri, 20 Mar 2026 03:44:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;please, collect all backtraces using echo t &amp;gt;/proc/sysrq-trigger &amp;amp; dmesg&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
