                            <comment id="491585" author="defazio" created="Thu, 19 Mar 2026 21:08:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;from the llnl ticket&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=behlendo&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;behlendo&quot;&gt;behlendo&lt;/a&gt; added a comment - yesterday- edited&lt;br/&gt;
Yuba5 encountered the same issue.&#160; The root cause appears to be a Lustre thread holding open a transaction which prevent the ZFS txg sync engine from being able to advance.&#160; This results in all of the Lustre threads waiting to assign new transactions causing a high load average but otherwise idle looking system.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;To check if a system has hit this issue the `/proc/spl/kstat/zfs/yuba5/txgs` file can be read to determine if TXGs are advancing.&#160; For example, the following output from yuba5 shows txg 54317256 is held open and is never allowed to close.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;54317252 614983271329207 &#160;C &#160; &#160; 5888512 &#160; &#160; &#160;8192 &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; 5537792 &#160; &#160; &#160;2 &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160;1066 &#160; &#160; 6303694 &#160; &#160; &#160;2795 &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; 32170 &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160;6818519&lt;br/&gt;
54317253 614983277632901 &#160;C &#160; &#160; 1213440 &#160; &#160; &#160;53248 &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160;2850816 &#160; &#160; &#160;13 &#160; &#160; &#160; 603 &#160; &#160; &#160;6893018 &#160; &#160; &#160;4659 &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; 28523 &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160;5790671&lt;br/&gt;
54317254 614983284525919 &#160;C &#160; &#160; 6722560 &#160; &#160; &#160;53248 &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160;5644288 &#160; &#160; &#160;11 &#160; &#160; &#160; 1078 &#160; &#160; 5843059 &#160; &#160; &#160;20228 &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160;27983 &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160;6899180&lt;br/&gt;
54317255 614983290368978 &#160;Q &#160; &#160; 0 &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160;0 &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160;0 &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160;0 &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160;0 &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160;6991544 &#160; &#160; &#160;0 &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160;0 &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160;0&lt;br/&gt;
54317256 614983297360522 &#160;O &#160; &#160; 0 &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160;0 &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160;0 &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160;0 &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160;0 &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160;0 &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160;0 &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160;0 &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160;0&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;From the yuba5 console looks it looks like pid 72193 is responsible for holding open the TX and waiting in llog_cat_declare_add_rec().&lt;/p&gt;

